    <name>
				<text>16.5.4.3 Find the Taylor series</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>Find the Taylor series expansion of \(\displaystyle {@exp@}\) about \(x={@x0@}.\) (That is, find a power series in powers of \( (x-{@x0@})\).)</p>
<p>Find the first three derivatives and the \(n^{th}\) derivative of \(\displaystyle f(x)={@exp@}\) and evaluate them at \( x_0= {@x0@} \):</p>
<p>Now obtain </p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">

    <li>
        <p>\(f'({@x0@}) =\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>
    </li>

    <li>
        <p>\(f''({@x0@}) =\) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>\(f'''({@x0@}) =\) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>\(f^{(n)}({@x0@}) =\) [[input:ans4]] [[validation:ans4]] [[feedback:prt4]]</p>
    </li>

</ol>

<p>Hence, obtain the Taylor series expansion of \(\displaystyle {@exp@}\) about \(x={@x0@}\) up to the 3rd power:</p>
<p>\(\displaystyle{@exp@}\approx \) [[input:ans5]][[validation:ans5]] [[feedback:prt5]]</p>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>We are aske to find theTaylor series expansion of \(\displaystyle {@exp@}\) about \(x={@x0@}.\)<br></p>
<p>First we find the derivatives of \(\displaystyle f(x)={@exp@}\) and evaluate them at \( x={@x0@}.\)</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
  <li><p>\(\displaystyle f'(x)= {@fprime1@} \Rightarrow&nbsp;f'({@x0@}) ={@ta1@} .\)</p></li>
<li><p><span style="font-size: 0.9375rem;">\(\displaystyle f''(x)= {@fprime2@} \Rightarrow&nbsp;f''({@x0@}) ={@ta2@} .\)</span></p></li>
<li><p><span style="font-size: 0.9375rem;">\(\displaystyle f'''(x)= {@fprime3@} \Rightarrow&nbsp;f'''({@x0@}) ={@ta3@} .\)</span><br></p></li>
<li><p>Generally \(\displaystyle f^{(n)}(x)= {@fgeneral@}\) so \(f^{(n)}({@x0@}) ={@ta4@}.\)</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Hence the Taylor expansion of \( \displaystyle {@exp@} \) is \[ {@exp@} = {@ta5@}\]</p>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
